import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=False)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=90)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['age'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['age'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average age of people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['age'] = pd.to_numeric(data['age'], errors='coerce')
    data['height'] = pd.to_numeric(data['height'], errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='age', y='height', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('Is there any correlation between age and height in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
